	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />As per the <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Cartridge_connector" class="postlink">wiki</a>, looks like you just connect CHR /A13 output to CIRAM /CE input, and tie CIRAM A10 input high or low (either gives you single-screen).<br /><br />In your schematic, the first connection is already made. It has pads for H and V mirroring. You could add another that has an option for tying &quot;VRAMA10&quot; to GND, in the lower right corner.

		

